text:
There's no way I could express our bond and our memories in few words of a memoir. But kyunki Memoir me kuch toh likhna hai toh here it goes.....
Oniiiii chaan !!! 

Lets start by thanking counselling service jiski vajah se hum dono mil paaye. There's no way two introverts like us, who wouldn't go around socialising with people, could meet each other in this vast world. But we did and it was awesome!! It's just been 2 years(jisme bhi 1 saal online ) but feels like I know you since a very very long time. We had such great times together. There were a lot of highs (literally ) and a lot of lows and we made our way through both of em together. We supported each other in the most crucial times and oh boy was the journey awesome!! 

While I'm writing this memoir, I recall that conversation we had in Goa regarding leaving each other and bruh I just dont feel like we'll ever leave each other ( just to reinforce (;P) ). You were there for me everytime I needed you and I always felt good about it because you're also the best person who can handle me üòú. Thanks for bearing with me all this time. I have learnt a lot of things from you!! 

Regarding the future, brother you know its all going to be okay and things will work out eventually!! And I know it will because I have seen you handle things that are so difficult to handle I have full belief in you that you will eventually figure everything out and make the best out of it. I have never seen a person who cares about ppl more than you do. You'd cross all the levels and overcome all the personal barriers to help other ppl and that's one of the qualities I like the most. 

Sorry for the couple of times I behaved very rudely and hurt you. I don't have any explanation and I know you don't jeed one either. 

Also its okay to commit mistakes sometimes. After seeing you handle very tough situations I had this image that this guy is a perfect person - has the purest soul and a will to help ppl so strong that he'll always help people. And it is true!! But you committing a mistake sometimes gives me hope - it tells me even a person as good as digu can commit mistakes - its a very human nature to commit mistakes and no one is perfect. But do know this brother you might not be the moon on the fill- moon day but you're the "chaudavin ka chaand" sorta - who may not be perfect but is closest among everyone else to being perfect!! 

What are you doing with life ? you're lifting spirits up of many people - many lonely people who would not approach anyone else for help although they should and they know they should. You've shown me there's a good and soft side to everyone and no person is evil and I cant forget that ever. You're someone I want to be like in terms of hooman affairs and I think enough time ke saath ho bhi jaau shayad. Thanks for giving me this hope ‚ò∫Ô∏è. 

Lmao a couple of months ago we were so clean in terms of bad habits and kya bakchod geera hai graph uske baad se!! I really hope we meet sooooner and get to do all that pending stuff!! If there is one thing I will forever be grateful for then that'd be meeting you!! Meeting you has been the been the best thing that has happened in my life till now and for some reason I think it will stay at that position forever. Don't know if I will find anything better after I have met you. I wouldn't mind going to the other world(heaven/ hell although pretty sure hum dono hell me hi jayenge saath me) after this bro!! ek aakhri aansu jab mere aankho se juda hone se takara rha tha tab uski peeth pe thap thapake usase "koi na behenchod, nikal le tu bhi" bolne wale insaan ko mera shat shat naman!!
Bhai memories ko ginte baithunga toh deadline nikal jayegi memoirs ki itni saari saari bakchodi jo kari hai saath me marte dam tk yaad rahegi ye sab!! 

 > gets out of room
> angdaiya lete hue " kya mast mausam hai behenchod" kehna
> not realising that the warden of the hall is passing by
> unki aankho me aankhe daalke dekhna while he passes by and listens to you saying " waah kya mast mausam hai behenchod"

> sits beside a small kid on antaragni stage
> zor se chillana " oy madarchod idhar aa"
> realising uss bachhe ki maa bhi uske sath baithi hai 
> stares inti mother's eyes 

> waiter ko baar baar bolne pe bhi paani nahi laaya 
> "idhar aana bhai zara" moment 
> phir 2 minute tak waiter ko galiyana 
> paani peene ke baad kuch bhi order na karke bahar nikal jaana 

Aise najaane kitne incidents rhe honge bhai but har incident me shrey jain khulke apne dil ki baat zamane ke saamne rakhte hue paata hu - aspass koi bhi ho bc. Will always remember wandering on IITK roads singing "meri bheegi bheegi si" with you. ngl one of my most favourite moments of all the walks I've had in campus. Thanks for the countless memories!! You were there till the last moment. Aisehi rehna bhai bakchodi karte hue. Milte hai kabhi wapas se ganne ka juice peene chalenge!!

To,
the Based Chairperson Gang,
Vrooooooooooooooo!!!!!
You're the wisest homie out of all the homies and ngl I really got to learn a lot from you. A wise man once said "you should not call someone your best friend because then you are comparing your friends and that is not good".  Ironically, the very first line of this memoir compares you with other people but okay. you are really a very awesome person and I am grateful that I got a chance to meet you in my life. I remember we met for the first time in first year summers lol. It was the phy103 AM thingy on which we worked together. I hate that we did not get to hang out in the last month of iitk. But hey, Gurgaon aur Noida ke beech kitna hi fasla hai lol. I really like how I could easily message you regarding how the Y18 is fucked up in ESC and we should do something and how easily we went on board and actually helped them. Thanks, for everything. text:
Hehe bro, 
ye memoir me kya hi likhu ab samajh nai aa rha. Jab bhi kuch kehna hota hai tumse mai toh seedha keh deta hu tumhe dont think aisa kuch hoga jo nahi keh paaya hounga. Thanks for giving me that space and trusting me at the same time. I remember that one time when you sensed that I might be overthinking things and might be in the guilt that I have messed up things. You knew I might be hurting myself just by overthinking on that and you sent me the most comforting text one could possibly send at that time. tbh I was really really scared at that time and you helped me. Life is weird no? Sometimes we help people and we think that it is a very small thing for us but it really means a lot to them. Thanks for that. Well this was just one incident, I think there a lot more incidents where you helped me when I wasn't doing okay, Even lockdown ke time me you were one of the very few people jinse meri har roz baat hoti thi and I think uska reason bhi obvious hai. You end up where you find most comfortable.  Thanks for existing. Thanks for everything. I will never forget the antaragni nights when we scrolled tinder together, the nights in sixth semester when we bonded and opened up to each other, that one whole night when we shared the gossips, the days when we planned out things together, the last night when you gave me that letter and other countless occasions. It was a very wonderful journey. A journey holistic journey in fact. I really enjoyed the journey and I hope you enjoyed it too!! Thanks for making it special. You are one of the few people I go to whenever I do not feel good and yet everytime you make me feel great about myself. Thanks for existing. I really hope we get to meet soon and complete all the pending pawris. All the best!! Also, I believe in you, no matter what other people say - I know you are a wonderful person and you  will achieve great things in life. Congratulations future Yashika for all the success!! Love you!!
